Package com.rb.biz.types.asset

Class AssetId

java.lang.Object
com.rb.biz.types.asset.AssetId
All Implemented Interfaces:
Investable, PrintsInstruments, HasLongRepresentation, java.lang.Comparable<HasLongRepresentation>
Direct Known Subclasses:
CashId, InstrumentId
public abstract class AssetId
extends java.lang.Object
implements Investable, PrintsInstruments
The base class for both CashId and InstrumentId.

AssetId is a concept that covers both instruments (securities) and cash. This allows us to have target allocations that don't special-case cash. However, in some cases, we only want to limit ourselves to cash. For example, an order to trade can never mention cash; we can't trade cash, whereas we can trade InstrumentIds.

There are many instances of InstrumentId, but only one kind of cash.

See Also:
CashId, InstrumentId
